pendencies (`ShippingService` and `CartService`).\n\n### Final JSON Output\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"SUPPORT\",\n  \"detected_trace_keys\": [\"latency_spike\", \"timeout\", \"checkoutservice->shippingservice\", \"checkoutservice->cartservice\"],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"checkoutservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"Maximum latency spike and specific errors from ShippingService and CartService.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"ShipOrder request latency increased dramatically from 14,434 ms (normal) to 2,513,904 ms (anomalous). Errors such as 'rpc error: code = Unavailable' and timeouts were observed, implicating Checkoutservice.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"shippingservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"Dependency failures when Checkoutservice interacted with ShippingService during the anomaly.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Significant latency increase (e.g., ShippingService's 'GetQuote' latency rising from 214 ms to 3681 ms) and timeout errors ('timed out waiting for server handshake').\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"cartservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"Anomalies in CartService operations, likely resulting from cascading failures.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Spike in latency noted, with CartService responses significantly delayed (e.g., increased operation time from 2462 ms to 10,664 ms and redis delays) during the anomaly period.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n``` \n\nThe hypothesis that \"checkoutservice is the root cause\" is strongly supported by the trace data investigation and related evidence. Further investigation may focus on the internal health and code handling in Checkoutservice and its dependency chains.", "current_hypothesis": "checkoutservice is the root cause due to maximum latency spike and specific errors from ShippingService."}
